Package it.polimi.se2018.view.gui

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AskDifficulty
    The controller for the screen that asks for difficulty in single-player mode.
    BoardEventPack
    This class holds some events that are changed often in the GameBoard class.
    Card
    This class handles the displaying of a card.
    DraftPoolFiller
    This class handles the display of the draft pool.
    GameBoard
    Abstract base JavaFX controller for the main game board.
    IncrementDieValueEventPack
    Set of events that are used when the player has to choose a die and whether to increment or decrement it.
    JavaFxDisplayer
    This class displays the game using a JavaFX gui.
    LoginView
    The controller to show the login view, which asks the username, the game mode and the type of connection.
    MoveDiceEventPack
    Set of events used when the player has to move two dices on its pattern.
    MultiPlayerBoard
    This class is a JavaFX controller for the multi player game board.
    Pattern
    This class is the JavaFX controller used when a pattern is displayed.
    PatternSelection
    The controller for the view that handles the pattern selection.
    PlaceDieEventPack  
    PrivateSelection
    There class to make the player handle the selection of the PrivateObjectiveCard at the beginning of the single-player game.
    RoundTrackFiller
    This class handles the display of the round track.
    ScoreBoard
    This class is a JavaFX controller to handle the display of the score board.
    SelectDieEventPack
    Set of events used when the player has to select a die from the draft pool.
    SelectValueEventPack
    Set of events used when the player has to select a value for the die and place it on its pattern.
    SinglePlayerBoard
    This class is a JavaFX controller for the single player game board.
    StandardEventPack
    Set of events regularly used by the player.
    SwapDiceEventPack
    Set of events used when the player has to select a die from the draft pool and a die from the round track.
    WaitingView
    Displays a window on the screen to tell that the user must wait a few moments before he can continue with the game.
